bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
under section 199 (1) (a) of the Act, the chief forester must specify the
                harvest profile for the volume-based portion as at the date that is
                immediately before the effective date of the Park Act deletion;

determine how much of the AAC reduction for the timber supply area is to
                be applied to the AAC available for BCTS licences by using the formula set
                out in section 203 of the Act;

as a result of the Park Act deletion, there is no practicable means by which
              the holder can access the cutting permit area or a portion of the cutting
              permit area;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
rights to harvest in the cutting permit area are cancelled by an order
                under section 26 [order to amend or cancel rights under cutting
                permit under area-based licence or non-TFL timber licence];

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
the rate of stumpage for timber authorized to be harvested under the cutting
              permit was determined, redetermined or varied using information provided
              by a relevant timber cruise;

references to section 244 [duty of cutting permit holder to provide
                information to minister] of the Act are to be read as references to section 36
                of this regulation;

the applicable impact date, in relation to a cutting permit compensation
                provision, is the effective date of the Park Act deletion to which the matter
                relates;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
a licence prescribed for the purposes of section 254 (1) (b)
                [compensation for road located outside special purpose area if road
                associated with cutting permit] of the Act;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
harvesting rights under the cutting permit are impacted, as a result of the
              Park Act deletion, in one of the ways described in section 53 of this
              regulation;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
harvesting under the cutting permit cannot reasonably be completed
              by harvesting timber from areas located outside the area that is
              subject to the Park Act deletion;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
in the case of harvesting rights impacted in the way set out in section 53 (a)
              of this regulation, the effective date of the order referred to in subparagraph
              (i) (A) or (B), as applicable, of that section;

rights in relation to the improvement are cancelled by an order under
            section 49 (1) (b) [order to amend or cancel rights in relation to road or
            improvement];
